# Environment Variables Template for Vercel + Neon

# Copy these to your Vercel project's Environment Variables section
# Go to: Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables

# =================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES
# =================

# Database Connection (get this from Neon after creating database)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@ep-xxx-xxx.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require

# Platform Detection (tells app it's running on Vercel)
VERCEL=1

# Security Key (generate a unique secret for production)
SECRET_KEY=ShastraBytes-Production-Secret-2025-Change-This

# =================
# OPTIONAL VARIABLES
# =================

# Database Performance Tuning
DATABASE_POOL_SIZE=5
DATABASE_MAX_OVERFLOW=10

# Flask Environment
FLASK_ENV=production
FLASK_DEBUG=false

# =================
# INSTRUCTIONS
# =================

# 1. Replace DATABASE_URL with your actual Neon connection string
# 2. Generate a strong SECRET_KEY for production
# 3. Add each line as a separate environment variable in Vercel
# 4. After adding all variables, redeploy your application

# =================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =================

# - Never commit actual credentials to Git
# - Use strong, unique SECRET_KEY for production
# - DATABASE_URL should include sslmode=require for security
# - Keep environment variables private in Vercel dashboard